      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EXTREMELY CHIC (4) got well out of her ground on debut before she warmed up late with an encouraging third over 1100m at this track in the heavy conditions. Desperate for this trip and further now and will prove hard to hold out. MISS SCANDAL (6) was well fancied when returning for her second prep before fading in the straight to finish fifth over 1100m at this track. Drops in weight today and will be better placed over this trip. Respect. EXCELLUNA (3) has race fitness on her side and finally drawn a good barrier today. Sat on the speed from the outside gate with a gritty fifth over 1100m at Warwick Farm. No surprise to see her take this out. SATIN SERENADE (8) is a Frankel filly out of the good producing mare Satin Ribbons on debut for the Waller yard. Has shown ability in all her trials and not to be underestimated.",
